    "title": "Bitfocus Companion: One Button, Your Entire Production",
    "category": "streaming",
    "date": "2026-02-17",
    "readTime": "5 min read",
    "metaDescription": "Bitfocus Companion turns your Stream Deck into a controller for your entire production — ATEM switcher, HyperDeck, PTZ cameras, audio, all from one button press. Here's how it works.",
    "excerpt": "Your ATEM switcher and your HyperDeck and your PTZ cameras don't talk to each other. Bitfocus Companion fixes that. One button, your entire production responds.",
    "image": "/images/blog/elgato-stream-deck-hero.jpg",
    "rating": 0,
    "price": "",
    "affiliateLink": "https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09738CV2G?tag=disbrowproduc-20",
    "asin": "B09738CV2G",
    "relatedProducts": [],
    "content": "<p>There's a problem in live production that nobody talks about directly: your gear doesn't talk to each other.</p>\n\n<p>Your ATEM switcher is doing its thing. Your HyperDeck is recording. Your PTZ cameras are on their own controller. Your audio console has its own interface. Your Stream Deck is sitting there running the Elgato app doing… not much. Each piece of equipment lives in its own world, controlled separately, requiring you or a crew member to touch each one individually when something needs to happen.</p>\n\n<p>Bitfocus Companion fixes this. One button press. Your entire production responds.</p>\n\n<h2>What Companion Actually Does</h2>\n\n<p>Companion is free software that runs on a computer on your network. It acts as the translator between your control surface — a Stream Deck, a touch screen, an iPad, any button panel — and any piece of hardware or software that has a Companion module.</p>\n\n<p>The module library is extensive. ATEM switchers. HyperDeck recorders. PTZ camera controllers. OBS. vMix. Dante audio. Presentation software. Lighting consoles. If the manufacturer or the community has built a plugin, Companion can talk to it.</p>\n\n<p>What this means practically: you build a button on your Stream Deck, assign it a sequence of actions across multiple devices, and push it once. Cut to camera two on the ATEM, start playback on the HyperDeck, trigger a lower third in your graphics system, bring up the pastor's mic channel on the audio console. One button. All of it.</p>\n\n<h2>The Real Value: Gear That Doesn't Normally Talk</h2>\n\n<p>The most powerful thing Companion does is bridge equipment that was never designed to communicate. Your ATEM switcher and your HyperDeck speak the same Blackmagic language. But your ATEM and your PTZ cameras? Your HyperDeck and your audio mixer? Companion is the middleware that connects them.</p>\n\n<p>This matters because live production is full of moments where multiple things need to happen simultaneously. A guest walks on stage — you need to cut to the wide shot, bring up their lavalier, and trigger a name graphic. In a traditional setup that's three operators or one operator trying to do three things at once. With Companion, it's one button press.</p>\n\n<p>The network reach extends this further. Companion runs on your local network, which means the control surface doesn't have to be at the switcher. A Stream Deck at the front-of-house audio position. An iPad in the director's hands on the floor. A button panel at the camera position for the operator to signal ready. Everyone in the production can trigger things from where they are.</p>\n\n<h2>It's as Advanced as You Need It to Be</h2>\n\n<p>The entry point is simple: one button, one action. Cut to input 3 on the ATEM. That takes five minutes to set up and immediately makes your Stream Deck useful in a way the Elgato software never could.</p>\n\n<p>From there, complexity scales exactly as much as your production demands. Multi-step macros. Conditional logic. Feedback that shows button states — green when recording is active, red when it stops. Scheduled triggers. Variables that pull live data from your devices and display them on button labels.</p>\n\n<p>A solo operator running a church stream might use ten buttons. A broadcast facility running Companion might have hundreds of triggers across a full control surface, automating entire segments of a live show.</p>\n\n<p>The learning curve is real — the interface takes some getting used to, and understanding the trigger/action/feedback model requires a few hours of experimentation. But the payoff is a production that runs on fewer people, with fewer errors, and with capabilities your gear manufacturer never intended you to have.</p>\n\n<h2>Where to Start</h2>\n\n<p>Download Companion free from bitfocus.io. Install it on any computer on your production network. Plug in your Stream Deck. Add a module for your ATEM. Build one button.</p>\n\n<p>If you're running a Blackmagic-based production and want to understand how Companion integrates with ATEM switchers and HyperDecks specifically — including the button layouts and macro sequences that actually get used in real church and live event productions — that's exactly what the ATEM School course covers.</p>\n\n<p>--- <em>Bitfocus Companion is free software. Stream Deck hardware is available on Amazon.</em></p>\n\n<div style=\"background:#EFF6FF;border:2px solid #BFDBFE;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.5rem;margin:2rem 0;text-align:center;\">\n  <p style=\"font-weight:700;color:#B91C1C;font-size:1.05rem;margin:0 0 0.5rem;\">Want the full Companion + ATEM workflow?</p>\n  <p style=\"color:#374151;margin:0 0 1rem;font-size:0.95rem;\">ATEM School covers how to integrate Companion with your full Blackmagic production — button layouts, macros, and real setups from live events.</p>\n  <div style=\"display:flex;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;\">\n    <a href=\"https://atemschool.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"display:inline-block;padding:0.7rem 1.5rem;background:#B91C1C;color:white;text-decoration:none;border-radius:0.5rem;font-weight:600;\">Learn at ATEM School →</a>\n    <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09738CV2G?tag=disbrowproduc-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"display:inline-block;padding:0.7rem 1.5rem;background:#fff;color:#B91C1C;text-decoration:none;border-radius:0.5rem;font-weight:600;border:2px solid #BFDBFE;\">Elgato Stream Deck on Amazon →</a>\n  </div>\n</div>"
